Japanese Bought Net 261.1 Billion Yen Overseas Debt Last Week

-- B y   T h e r e s a   B a r r a c l o u g h
-- 
2011-12-08T00:04:48Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-08/japanese-bought-net-261-1-billion-yen-overseas-debt-last-week.html
Japanese investors were net
buyers of foreign bonds during the week ended Dec. 2 according to
figures based on reports from designated major investors released by
the Ministry of Finance in  Tokyo .  Japanese investors bought 261.1 billion yen ($3.4 billion)
in overseas bonds and notes, bought 89.9 billion yen in overseas stocks
and sold 150.3 billion yen in overseas short term securities.
That results in a total net purchase of 200.7 billion yen.  Foreign investors sold 222.4 billion yen in Japanese bonds,
bought 59 billion yen in stocks, and bought 314.9 billion yen in
short term securities, resulting in a total net purchase of 151.5
billion yen.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Theresa Barraclough in Tokyo at   tbarraclough@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Marco Babic at   mbabic@bloomberg.net  